review_blob: Cask at Olde Bull & Bush, Stoke. Pours copper with an off white head. Autumnal berry, light hop, some toffee. OK, similar to Rev James but not as good.
Cask at White Star, Stoke. Quite a boozy, tart IPA. Some resinous hop but booziness overpowers it.
Cask at Blue Bell, Annan. Pours golden with off white head. Quite a sweet sticky well balanced amber. Easy drinking.
Cask at Congress, Longton. Pours golden with an off white head. Light citrus, some biscuit. Boring as hell.
Cask at Congress, Longton. Pours golden with an off white head. Some orange, resinous hop, malt, more hop. Pleasant session gold.
Keg at Herrnbrau brauhaus, Ingolstadt. Pours caramel brown with an off white head. Sweet, some plum, more sweetness, too much so. Alcohol kick.
Keg at Herrnbrau brauhaus, Ingolstadt. Pours murky brown with an off white froth. Some banana, clove, caramel sweetness, not bad.
Keg at Herrnbrau brauhaus, Ingolstadt. Pours golden haze with an off white froth. Very dull wheat beer, some spice, nothing else kicking in.
Keg at Inter City Hotel, Ingolstadt. Pours golden with white froth. Quite a dry, grassy bog standard pils.
Keg at SV Sandhausen. Pours pale gold with white froth. Quite a citrus led hoppy pils. Better than I expected.
Keg at Frankurt Airport. Pours golden with a white head. A bit too gassy, some caramel, nicely hopped. Not a bad helles.
Cask at Crosse Keys (JDW), Gracechurch St. Pours golden with a white head. Some lemon, light spice, little thin, OK session rye.
Cask at Crosse Keys (JDW), Gracechurch St. Pours chestnut with off white head. Some dry berry fruit, caramel, bitter finish. Solid bitter.
Cask at Crosse Keys (JDW), Gracechurch St. Pours golden with an off white head. A little thin, light on hops, average really.
Cask at Crosse Keys (JDW), Gracechurch St. Pours black brown with light tan head. Nice creamy milk chocolate, touch of coffee, butterscotch. Decent body. Good stuff.
Cask at Draft House Seething, London. Pours chestnut with off white head. Nice dry session bitter. Pleasant enough.
Cask at Draft House Seething, London. Pours black brown with a red hue. Decent enough stout but wheres the raspberry? Disappointing.
Keg at Draft House Seething, London. Pours golden with a slight haze. Nice resinous IPA style rye. Some spice. Decent.
Keg at Draft House Seething, London. Pours blackcurrant red with a pink head. Tobacco, some sour, hint of blackcurrant. Looking forward to this but disappointed.

beer_brewer_name: Ross On Wye Cider & Perry (Broome Farm)
review_blob: Gravity at Euston Cider Tap. Pours apple yellow brown. Dry apple, tart bitterness. Smooth sugar.
Draught at Euston Cider Tap. Pours pale gold, sugary cut water. Farmyard, sweet sugar, average.
Cask at Plume of Feathers, Barlaston. Pours golden with stiff white head. Very bitter, boring golden ale. Bitter, hard work.
Cask at Head of Steam, Lilbourne. Pours amber with an off white head. Pretty basic stuff, overpowered with crystal malt.
Cask at Head of Steam, Lilbourne. Pours black red brown with a tan head. Creamy, oatmeal stout. Some cocoa. Decent.
Keg at Ways Green Conservative Club, Winsford. Pours caramel brown with an off white head. Sweet, creamy, nutty, not bad for a mass produced keg mild.
Cask at Weavers, Strathaven. Pours golden with a white head. Starts Ok, nice bitterness, bit of butterscotch. Then goes very sweet, sickly in the end.
Cask at Moo Bar, Penrith. Pours amber with an off white head. Quite malty, berry fruit, bitter. Good session ale.

Cask at Moo Bar, Penrith. Well this is what I reckon I had, pump clip said Pale and so did the barrel. It wasnt pale and didnt taste of chinook and cascade hops, so theyve put the wrong beer in the barrel. Smooth stout, little underwhelming taste wise but OK nonetheless.
Keg at Moo Bar, Penrith. Pours golden with a white head. Fizzy standard English pale, pffft.
Keg at Moo Bar, Penrith. Pours black brown with a tan head. Fizz, roast, cocoa, milk, oaty. Good keg stout.
Cask at Moo Bar, Penrith. Pours black brown with tan head. Plenty of coffee, cool espresso, creamy, some lickadick, roast. Good stuff.
Cask at Moo Bar, Penrith. Its actually Doctor Gulleys with an e. Pours golden with an off white head. Dull boring golden beer, nothing like its deScription. Its Ok if you want an average beer.
Cask at Black Lion, Consall Forge. Now 4.8%, pour dark brown with a light tan head. Full bodied porter but there is no real hop presence. Smooth, malty , creamy porter.
Bottle from Otters Tears, Burslem. Pours hazy golden orange with a huge white froth. Nice and hoppy, some brett, sharp finish. I liked this and Im not a great fan of saisons.
Bottle from Otters Tears, Burslem. Pours cola brown with a tan wisp. Harsh booze, some brett, little hop. All over the place. Cant taste the damsons.
Keg at The Coach, Bridgend. Pours murky amber. Very dry, well hopped, some caramel. Not bad.
Cask at The Coach, Bridgend. Pours dark golden with an off white head. Very bitter, dry, hint of citrus. Decent bitter rather than a golden.
Cask at The Coach, Bridgend. Pours ruby with an off white head. Light spice, nice bitterness, bit dry, maybe too thin. Pleasant.
Bottle from Otters Tears, Burslem. Pours murky amber with off white head. Some sweet dark fruit, sour brett, more sweetness. Good
Bottle from Otters Tears, Burslem. Pours mud brown with an off white head. Some smoked sausage, sweet caramel, well balanced. Good stuff.
Bottle from Otters Tears, Burslem. Pours cola black with a fast diminishing tan head. Prune, sour, some coffee, more sourness. Good stuff.
Bottle from Otters Tears, Burslem. Pours very pale gold with white head. Bit watery, some yoghurt, not very sour really. Pleasant enough.
Cask at Bursley Ale House, Burslem. Pours chestnut with off white head. Quite a sweet fruity start, some bitterness, dies on its arse though.
Cask at Bursley Ale House, Burslem. Pours black brown with tan head. More of a hoppy porter than a stout. Good body for its strength, light hop, some choc. Good.
Cask at The Forge, Brierley Hill. Pours caramel brown with an off white head. Tasted dry and industrial before it settled. Some caramel, bread, OK average mild.
Cask at Bree Louise, Euston. Pours black brown with a tan whisp. Thin porter, weird sweet lime dollop, face puller. Weird and I dont think it was served in the best condition.
Keg at The Rake. Pours golden orange with a white head. Plenty of berry, resinous hop, smooth, alcohol tinge. Good stuff.
beer_name: Weird Beard / BrewDog Shepherds Bush Safeword

review_blob: Keg at The Rake. Pours hazy golden with a white froth. Little yeast, some orange, bitter finish. OK.
Keg at the brewery. Pours pink with an off white froth. Not really a saison in taste, loads of raspberry with a sharp sour lemon finish. Cracking fruit beer.
Keg at the brewery. Pours golden haze with white head. Pucker up, decent sharp gose. Light fruit, zap.
